# StackOpen 🚀

A Stack Overflow-inspired Q&A community platform for developers. Ask questions, share knowledge, vote on answers, and grow together.

## 🌐 Live Demo

https://stackopen.netlify.app/

## ✨ Features

- 📝 Ask and answer questions
- 🏷️ Tag-based communities
- 🏆 Leaderboard with reputation scores
- 👤 User profiles with edit functionality
- 🌙 Dark/Light mode toggle
- 🔍 Search questions and communities
- 🗑️ Delete your own questions and answers

## 🛠️ Tech Stack

- **Frontend:** HTML, CSS, Vanilla JavaScript
- **Backend/Database:** [Supabase](https://supabase.com) (PostgreSQL)
- **Hosting:** Netlify
- **Icons:** Font Awesome 6

## 📁 Project Structure

```
frontend/
├── css/
│   └── style.css          # Main stylesheet
├── js/
│   ├── api.js             # Supabase API calls
│   ├── auth.js            # Auth logic (login/signup/logout)
│   ├── main.js            # App initialization
│   └── posts.js           # Post/answer rendering & voting
├── index.html             # Home feed
├── post.html              # Single post detail
├── create-post.html       # Ask a question
├── profile.html           # User profile
├── tags.html              # Communities/tags list
├── community.html         # Single community page
├── leaderboard.html       # Top contributors
├── login.html             # Login page
└── signup.html            # Signup page
```

## 🗄️ Database Schema (Supabase)

### Tables:

**posts**
```sql
id          BIGSERIAL PRIMARY KEY
title       TEXT NOT NULL
body        TEXT NOT NULL
tags        TEXT[]
author      TEXT
votes       INT DEFAULT 0
is_answered BOOLEAN DEFAULT false
created_at  TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW()
```

**answers**
```sql
id         BIGSERIAL PRIMARY KEY
post_id    BIGINT REFERENCES posts(id) ON DELETE CASCADE
body       TEXT NOT NULL
author     TEXT
votes      INT DEFAULT 0
created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW()
```

**users**
```sql
id         BIGSERIAL PRIMARY KEY
username   TEXT UNIQUE NOT NULL
email      TEXT
score      INT DEFAULT 0
level      TEXT DEFAULT 'Beginner'
created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW()
```

**votes**
```sql
id         BIGSERIAL PRIMARY KEY
user_id    TEXT NOT NULL
post_id    BIGINT REFERENCES posts(id) ON DELETE CASCADE
answer_id  BIGINT REFERENCES answers(id) ON DELETE CASCADE
vote_type  TEXT CHECK (vote_type IN ('upvote', 'downvote'))
created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW()
UNIQUE(user_id, post_id)
UNIQUE(user_id, answer_id)
```

## 🚀 Getting Started

### 1. Clone the repo
```bash
git clone https://github.com/your-username/stackopen.git
cd stackopen/frontend
```

### 2. Open locally
Just open `index.html` in your browser — no build step needed!

Or use Live Server in VS Code for the best experience.

### 3. Set up your own Supabase (optional)
If you want your own database:
1. Create a free project at [supabase.com](https://supabase.com)
2. Run the SQL schema above in the SQL Editor
3. Replace `SUPABASE_URL` and `SUPABASE_KEY` in `js/api.js`

## 📦 Deploying to Netlify

1. Push this repo to GitHub
2. Go to [netlify.com](https://netlify.com) → "Add new site" → "Import from Git"
3. Select your GitHub repo
4. Set **Base directory** to `frontend`
5. Click **Deploy** — done!

